6. To prepare the students in order to understand the city planning features in a wide range of subjects related with city analysis at the European scale.

The objectives of this course are to increase understanding and knowledge about the start-ups, entrepreneurship, entrepreneurial organization, and governance issues in firms. The students will learn basic elements in how to start a business and governance issues in small firms.
Skills to be acquired by the student:
- Characterize the Company and it fits in its environment;
- Know the process of creating new companies, factors and conditions
- Recognize and evaluate business ideas opportunities;
- Develop and propose a business idea;
- Know the Organization, Structure and Functions of the Company;
- Develop and present a report of the Company

The program aims to:
- Promote historical and theoretical analysis of 21st century architecture paradigms, namely about new contexts and new models and scales, resulting from contemporary cultural, social, economic and political phenomena in constant transformation;
- Rethink the sense of community, promoting new uses and operating dynamics, adapted to a specific culture;
- Explore different design processes and methodologies for architectural design adapted to different cultures.
At the end of the practical exercise, students should demonstrate that they were able to:
- Understand and characterize the natural, urban, historical and social context of a provided location;
- Understand and characterize the specificity of the morphological, orographic and topographic situation of that location;
- Propose a solution appropriate to the context and the assumptions made by a promoter;
- Propose a constructive characterization appropriate to the context and the program.

